**Steps to run spring boot app**


docker pull mongodb/mongodb-community-server:7.0.8-ubuntu2204
docker run --name mongodb -p 27017:27017 -d mongodb/mongodb-community-server:latest

1) install java 21
2) install maven tool
3) install intellij editor community edition
4) open the project in intellij ide

To run database
1) install docker
2) open command prompt and run the below command
 docker-compose up -d
3) run cmd _docker ps_ in console to see if both containers are running

H2-CONSOLE:
-----------
http://localhost:8080/h2-console

Once docker is up and running with postgres db
run java application in intellij ide


//-- api docs
//------ api related to user

login user :
    POST /api/login
register user:
    POST /api/register
change pasword
    PUT /api/user/changepwd/
update user:
    PUT /api/user
add address
    POST /api/user/address
update address
    PUT /api/user/address
delete user
    DELETE /api/user

